  'illinois': { name: 'Illinois', abbr: 'IL', icon: '\u{1f3d9}\ufe0f', topics: ['Chicago RLTO', 'Property Tax', 'Business Law', 'Tenant Rights'], content: 'Illinois, particularly Chicago, has the Residential Landlord Tenant Ordinance (RLTO) with strong tenant protections. The state has complex tax structures and business regulations.\n\n## Key Legal Areas in Illinois\n\n### Chicago RLTO\nChicago has one of the most comprehensive tenant protection ordinances in the country, the Residential Landlord Tenant Ordinance (RLTO). It requires specific disclosures, limits on security deposits, and additional tenant rights.\n\n### Property Tax\nIllinois has complex property tax systems with multiple taxing districts and assessment procedures. The state has some of the highest property tax rates in the nation.\n\n### Business Law\nIllinois has specific business regulations including the Illinois Business Corporation Act and various licensing requirements.\n\n### Employment Law\nIllinois follows at-will employment but has specific protections including the Illinois Human Rights Act and recent amendments regarding employee rights.', keyLaws: ['Illinois Residential Landlord and Tenant Act', 'Illinois Business Corporation Act', 'Illinois Human Rights Act', 'Chicago Residential Landlord and Tenant Ordinance (RLTO)'], legalNotes: ['Chicago RLTO provides strong tenant protections', 'Security deposit interest required in Chicago', '5-day notice for non-payment of rent', 'Just cause eviction in Chicago'] },
